# Dashboard hub forms

Reference when adding or changing **Models hub**, **Fetch Financials hub**, or shared **`ChipInput`** / **`hubFormValidation`** behavior.

## Shared conventions

| Rule | Detail |
|------|--------|
| Submit buttons | Always clickable except while a request is **in flight** (`loading`). Never disable for empty required fields. |
| Missing required | Show banner: **"Please fill all required values."** (`FILL_REQUIRED_MSG` in `frontend/src/utils/hubFormValidation.ts`) |
| Field highlight | Every missing/invalid **required** field gets a **red border** (`inputFieldClass` / `ChipInput error`) until the user edits it. |
| Chip placeholder | Input bar always shows: `Type ticker and press enter` (sentence case, not ALL CAPS). |
| Chip labels | Show limit on the **label**: e.g. `Peers (up to 5)`, `Tickers (up to 5)`. Do not repeat long helper paragraphs above the field. |
| Max items | Do not show a permanent "max N" hint under the chip bar. On add over limit, show inline amber hint (`Maximum N items`). |
| Ticker typing | No forced uppercase while typing; normalize to uppercase on submit / chip commit. Placeholders use lowercase examples (`e.g. aapl`, `e.g. nvda`). |
| In-flight UX | Use shared in-flight maps (`sessionModels.ts`, `sessionFinancials.ts`, `sessionRag.ts`) so navigation away does not reset loading state. |

## Models hub — DCF tab

| Field | Required | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Model name | Yes | Red border if empty on Create |
| Ticker | No | Optional; fetches 5Y SEC reference when set |
| Projection years | Yes | Default `5`; red border if not 1–10 |
| Base revenue ($M) | No | If typed, must be valid number or red border + specific message |
| Button | `Create template` | → `POST /api/sessions/{id}/models/dcf` |

## Models hub — Comparative tab

| Field | Required | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Model name | No | Custom name; if omitted backend names `{target} vs {peer1} vs …` |
| Target | Yes | **Ticker only** (no company-name resolution); red border if empty |
| Peers | Yes (1–5) | `ChipInput`, tickers only; red border if empty on submit |
| Button | `Do comparative analysis` | → `POST /api/sessions/{id}/models/comparative` |

Backend: `create_comparative_model` in `backend/services/comparative.py` — fail-fast SEC fetch, max 5 peers.

## Fetch Financials hub

| Field | Required | Notes |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Tickers | Yes (up to 5) | `ChipInput`; red border if empty on Fetch |
| Fiscal years | No | Up to 10 chips |
| Last N fiscal years | No | Disabled when specific year chips are set |
| Button | `Fetch financials` | → `POST /api/sessions/{id}/financials/fetch` |

